The week in 28 photos|http://www.cnn.com/world|http://www.cnn.com/2018/08/30/world/gallery/week-in-photos-0831/index.html||2018-08-30|||Rohingya girls share a laugh Sunday, August 26, at the Kutupalong refugee camp in Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh. A year ago, hundreds of thousands of Rohingya Muslims started fleeing from Myanmar into what has become the world's biggest refugee camp. Many of those who crossed the border have recounted horrific stories of being driven from their homes under threat of death. Myanmar's military has repeatedly denied that it has deliberately attacked unarmed Rohingya. Instead, the authorities insist that it only targets Rohingya militants.
